In favor of the Mobile commerce on every 25 tons weight to Knox|ville 9,384 doll.</P>
<P>From Na&s;hville on Cumberland river, to the head navigation of the South &s;treams of Tenne&s;&s;ee, neare&s;t Mobile Bay, is about 460 miles, by water; time of pa&s;&s;age to and from &s;a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d ports with a boat of 25 tons bur|then, will be about 45 days; with the a&s;&s;i&s;tance of ten hands, at one dollar per day each, is 450 dollars.</P>
<P>From Mobile Bay to the neare&s;t navigable waters of Tenne&s;&s;ee river as per letter X 800 dollars.</P>
