<P>V</P>
<P>From the mouth of Mi&s;&s;i&s;&s;ippi, to the mouth of Ohio by water; is com|puted to be about 1,000 miles&mdash;
<PB N="7" REF="035360_0007_10049F4CF8BAEF18">time of pa&s;&s;age to and from &s;aid ports, with a boat of 25 tons bur|then, will be about 100 days&mdash;with the a&s;&s;i&s;tance of 20 hands, at one dollar per day each, is 2,000 dolls.</P>
<P>From the junction of the Obio and Mi&s;&s;i&s;&s;ippi, to the head navigation of the South &s;treams of Tenne&s;&s;ee river, neare&s;t Mobile Bay, is about 300 miles, time of pa&s;&s;age to and from &s;aid points, will be about 30 days; with the a&s;&s;i&s;tance of 10 hands, at one dollar per day, is 300 dollars.</P>
<P>From Mobile Bay, to the neare&s;t navigable waters of Tenne&s;&s;ee, as per letter X 800 dollars.</P>
<P>Total expence on 25 tons weight, from Mobile Bay to the mouth of O|hio and back again. 1,100 dolls.</P>
<P>In favor of the Mobile commerce; owing to the turbulency, of the Mi&s;|&s;i&s;&s;ippi current. 900 dollars.</P>
<P>From the mouth of Ohio river to Knoxville, in the State of Tenne&s;&s;ee, is about 650 miles&mdash;time of pa&s;&s;ing to and from the &s;aid ports, with a boat of 25 tons burthen, will be about &s;ixty five days; with the a&s;&s;i&s;tance of ten hands at one dol|lar per day each, is 650 dollars.</P>
